<paragraph blockId="8.[189,310,1771,1797]" box="[189,310,1771,1797]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1771,1797]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1771,1797]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[188,1399,1819,2025]" lastBlockId="9.[188,1399,265,469]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Recognized by the following combination of characters: body narrow, parallel-sided, pronotum at base less than 1.5× as wide as head (
<figureCitation box="[554,686,1855,1881]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="43.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[255,1348,414,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-12@43.[189,1398,376,1856]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="Fig. 2. Habitus of Ernestinus, Harpedona and Lopidolon spp. A. Ernestinus mimicus Distant, 1911, ♂, UASB. B. Ernestinus ramkeshariae Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa, 2016, ♂, UASB. C. Harpedona sanguinipes Distant, 1904, ♂, UASB. D. Harpedona vittlaensis sp. nov, ♀, UASB. E–F. Lopidolon dandeliensis sp. nov., UASB. E. ♂. F. ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690366" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690366/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs 2C–D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[697,769,1854,1881]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="46.[189,232,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[263,1330,330,1736]" captionTargetId="figure-17@46.[189,1398,297,1786]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="Fig. 5. Dorsal view and label data of type specimens. A–C. Dioclerus bengalicus Stonedahl, 1988, ♀, holotype, BPBM.D–E. Dioclerus lutheri Stonedahl, 1988, ♂, holotype, AMNH_PBI 00338430, FMNH. F–G. Dioclerus praefectus Distant,1910, lectotype, AMNH_PBI 00340384, NHM. H–I. Ernestinus mimicus Distant,1911, ♂, syntype, AMNH_PBI 00085668, BMNH(E) 1633157, NHM. J–K. Harpedona marginata Distant, 1904, ♂, holotype, NHM. L–M. Harpedona sanguinipes Distant, 1909, ♂, lectotype, NHM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690372" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690372/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">5J–M</figureCitation>
); coloration of dorsum uniform, dirty yellow to black, sometimes with paler embolium, legs contrastingly whitish or reddish yellow, comparatively long and slender, apex of hind femur reaching or surpassing apex of abdomen; dorsum clothed with dense, short, adpressed, silvery simple setae; pronotal collar wide and large; calli medially confluent, dorsally and laterally separated by deep impressed lines giving appearance of three distinct sections of pronotum; genital capsule highly modified, with large, lobate process on right margin, and usually with bulbous, twisted and spinelike outgrowths on dorsal margin (
<figureCitation box="[788,933,300,327]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="55.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[310,1285,295,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-52@55.[227,1360,265,1889]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="Fig. 14. Male genitalia of Harpedona marginata Distant, 1904, NHM. A–C. Genital capsule in ventral and lateral views. D–E. Right paramere in dorsal and lateral views. F. Right paramere in dorsal view. G. Aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690392" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690392/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs 14A–C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[944,1031,300,327]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="56.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[209,1328,425,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-57@56.[189,1398,401,1890]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Fig. 15. Male genitalia of Harpedona sanguinipes Distant, 1904, UASB. A–B. Genital capsule in dorsal and ventral views. C–D. Left paramere in lateral view. E–F. Right paramere in dorsal view. G–H. Aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690395/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">15A–B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1042,1096,300,327]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="57.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[302,1333,446,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-53@57.[189,1398,408,1890]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="Fig. 16. Male genitalia of Harpedona vittlaensis sp. nov., holotype, UASB. A. Genital capsule in lateral view. B–C. Left paramere in dorsal and lateral views. D–E. Right paramere in dorsal and lateral views. F. Aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690397" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690397/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">16A</figureCitation>
); parameres and aedeagus reduced, very small; left paramere with long and thin, twisted apical process (
<figureCitation box="[1141,1289,336,362]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="55.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[310,1285,295,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-52@55.[227,1360,265,1889]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="Fig. 14. Male genitalia of Harpedona marginata Distant, 1904, NHM. A–C. Genital capsule in ventral and lateral views. D–E. Right paramere in dorsal and lateral views. F. Right paramere in dorsal view. G. Aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690392" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690392/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs 14D–E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1305,1392,336,363]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="56.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[209,1328,425,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-57@56.[189,1398,401,1890]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Fig. 15. Male genitalia of Harpedona sanguinipes Distant, 1904, UASB. A–B. Genital capsule in dorsal and ventral views. C–D. Left paramere in lateral view. E–F. Right paramere in dorsal view. G–H. Aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690395/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">15C–D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[189,277,371,398]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="57.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[302,1333,446,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-53@57.[189,1398,408,1890]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="Fig. 16. Male genitalia of Harpedona vittlaensis sp. nov., holotype, UASB. A. Genital capsule in lateral view. B–C. Left paramere in dorsal and lateral views. D–E. Right paramere in dorsal and lateral views. F. Aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690397" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690397/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">16B–C</figureCitation>
); right paramere simple, with tapering incurved apex (
<figureCitation box="[914,1020,371,397]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="55.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[310,1285,295,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-52@55.[227,1360,265,1889]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="Fig. 14. Male genitalia of Harpedona marginata Distant, 1904, NHM. A–C. Genital capsule in ventral and lateral views. D–E. Right paramere in dorsal and lateral views. F. Right paramere in dorsal view. G. Aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690392" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690392/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs 14F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1032,1111,371,398]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="56.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[209,1328,425,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-57@56.[189,1398,401,1890]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Fig. 15. Male genitalia of Harpedona sanguinipes Distant, 1904, UASB. A–B. Genital capsule in dorsal and ventral views. C–D. Left paramere in lateral view. E–F. Right paramere in dorsal view. G–H. Aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690395/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">15E–F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1123,1211,371,398]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="57.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[302,1333,446,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-53@57.[189,1398,408,1890]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="Fig. 16. Male genitalia of Harpedona vittlaensis sp. nov., holotype, UASB. A. Genital capsule in lateral view. B–C. Left paramere in dorsal and lateral views. D–E. Right paramere in dorsal and lateral views. F. Aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690397" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690397/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">16D–E</figureCitation>
); aedeagus with entirely membranous phallotheca, simple membranous endosoma and sclerotized, spine-like apical part of ductus seminis (
