, 
<figureCitation box="[534,623,442,469]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="56.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[209,1328,425,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-57@56.[189,1398,401,1890]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Fig. 15. Male genitalia of Harpedona sanguinipes Distant, 1904, UASB. A–B. Genital capsule in dorsal and ventral views. C–D. Left paramere in lateral view. E–F. Right paramere in dorsal view. G–H. Aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690395/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">15G–H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[635,685,442,469]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="57.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[302,1333,446,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-53@57.[189,1398,408,1890]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="Fig. 16. Male genitalia of Harpedona vittlaensis sp. nov., holotype, UASB. A. Genital capsule in lateral view. B–C. Left paramere in dorsal and lateral views. D–E. Right paramere in dorsal and lateral views. F. Aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690397" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690397/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">16F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,342,507,533]" box="[189,342,507,533]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,342,507,533]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,342,507,533]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[186,1398,554,617]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Known from 
<collectingCountry box="[342,457,554,580]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, southwestern and northern 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Poppius" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[777,837,554,580]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="India" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">India</taxonomicName>
to Fukien Prov. of 
<collectingCountry box="[1051,1124,554,580]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1133,1268,554,580]" name="Philippines" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1277,1394,554,580]" name="Indonesia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, New 
<collectingCountry box="[249,337,590,616]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, and the 
<collectingCountry box="[441,638,590,616]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stonedahl G. M." box="[653,843,590,616]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 99" refId="ref23015" refString="Stonedahl G. M. 1988. Revisions of Dioclerus, Harpedona, Mertila, Myiocapsus, Prodromus and Thaumastomiris (Heteroptera: Miridae, Bryocorinae: Eccritotarsini). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 187: 1 - 99." type="journal article" year="1988">Stonedahl 1988</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,303,656,682]" box="[189,303,656,682]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,656,682]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,656,682]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[188,1401,702,906]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
This genus was revised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stonedahl G. M." box="[517,723,702,729]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 99" refId="ref23015" refString="Stonedahl G. M. 1988. Revisions of Dioclerus, Harpedona, Mertila, Myiocapsus, Prodromus and Thaumastomiris (Heteroptera: Miridae, Bryocorinae: Eccritotarsini). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 187: 1 - 99." type="journal article" year="1988">Stonedahl (1988)</bibRefCitation>
and, with addition of the recently described 
<taxonomicName authority="Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa, 2016" authorityName="Yasunaga" authorityYear="2016" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Harpedona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stonedahli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Harpedona stonedahli</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yasunaga Y. &amp; Ishikawa T." box="[317,647,738,764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="411 - 469" refId="ref23196" refString="Yasunaga Y. &amp; Ishikawa T. 2016. Twelve new species of the Asian plant bug genus Ernestinus Distant (Heteroptera: Miridae: Bryocorinae: Eccritotarsini), with emphasis on unique biology and descriptions of three additional new eccritotarsine species. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution 47 (5): 411 - 469. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 1876312 X- 47052149" type="journal article" year="2016">Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, it currently comprises 13 species. Only 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant, 1909" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Harpedona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinipes">
<emphasis box="[1117,1397,738,764]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Harpedona sanguinipes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Distant W. L." box="[188,351,773,799]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="440 - 454" refId="ref21497" refString="Distant W. L. 1909. Descriptions of Oriental Capsidae. Annals and Magazine of Natural History 8 (4): 440 - 454. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930908692696" type="journal article" year="1909">Distant, 1909</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was known from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Poppius" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[579,639,773,799]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="India" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">India</taxonomicName>
prior to our study; the description of a new species from the 
<collectingRegion box="[189,376,809,835]" country="India" name="Karnataka" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Karnataka state</collectingRegion>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Poppius" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[425,485,809,835]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="India" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">India</taxonomicName>
is given below. 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant, 1904" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1904" box="[697,1143,809,835]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Harpedona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis box="[697,964,809,835]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Harpedona marginata</emphasis>
Distant, 1904
</taxonomicName>
, the most frequently collected and widely distributed species of the genus was originally described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1175,1290,844,870]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
and may likely be found in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Poppius" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[404,464,880,906]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="India" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">India</taxonomicName>
with more sampling effort.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,961,945,972]" box="[189,961,945,972]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,961,945,972]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,961,945,972]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Key to species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1904" box="[530,667,945,972]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Harpedona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[530,667,945,972]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Harpedona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Poppius" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[706,773,945,971]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="India" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">India</taxonomicName>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[834,961,945,971]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
